description: A Chromium-based WPF/WinForms component that can be embedded into your .NET application to display modern web pages built with HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript, Silverlight etc.
releaseNotes:
DotNetBrowser 1.6.1 contains the following features and improvements:
			XPath support has been implemented.
			Video support (HTML5, Flash, Silverlight) has been improved.
			The issue with NullReferenceException thrown during initialization on Windows 8/8.1/10  has been fixed.
			Stability of WinForms/WPF BrowserView control in MS Visual Studio WinForms/XAML UI Designer has been improved.
			Several thread deadlock issues during Browser instantiation/disposal have been fixed.
summary: Solution for integration of Chromium-based component into .NET applications.
title: DotNetBrowser
